707413f-a.text:
Willow & Poplar St., Bklyn., 1ooking east. Federal Art Project, "Changing New York,' photographs by
Berenice Abbott. Negative #119.
May 1, 1936
707413f-a.folder: Willow St. & Poplar St., Brooklyn, NY

706304f-a.text:
Poplar Street, west from Willow Street to Columbia Heights, where it terminates. The 3-story house, in the center, is on the latter street. In the background is the lower Manhattan skyline, the buildings (from left to right) being the City Bank Farmers Trust, the Bank of Manhattan and the 60 Wall Tower.

About 1939

Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad, A. R. P. S.
706304f-a.folder: Poplar Street & Willow Street, Brooklyn, NY

706308f-a.text:
32-34 Poplar Street, south side, between Willow and Hicks Streets, as seen from McKenney Street.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
706308f-a.folder: Poplar Street & Willow Street, Brooklyn, NY

1-11 Willow Street, east side, south from Poplar Street ; No. 1, at Poplar Street, is invisible. Also seen is 21-23 Poplar Street, at the foot of Willow Street, between Columbia Heights and McKenney Street.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same; showing only Nos. 1-3 Willow Street, with Poplar Street,
south side, east from Willow to Hicks Streets.
April 4, 1932.
